ðŸ”¹ What is a Thread?

A thread = a unit of execution.

Think like this:

If 100 users call your API at same time,
Spring server creates 100 threads to handle them.

You donâ€™t manually create threads in Spring normally.

Just understand:
	â€¢	One request = one thread (usually)
	â€¢	Threads allow multiple users at same time

Basic Example :

public class ThreadExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Runnable task = () -> {
            System.out.println("Hello from " + Thread.currentThread().getName());
        };

        Thread t = new Thread(task);
        t.start();
    }
}

Thatâ€™s enough.

You donâ€™t need deep multithreading now.

